# Copy to .env.local for local development (used by `vercel dev`). Never
# commit real values — see .gitignore.
#
# The server-side pieces below run as Vercel Serverless Functions under
# /api — see ARCHITECTURE.md's "Payment completion pipeline". A secret key
# must never be a VITE_-prefixed variable, since Vite inlines every VITE_
# variable into the public client bundle.

# --- Client-safe (VITE_ prefixed — inlined into the public bundle) ---
# Stripe's publishable key (pk_*) — safe to expose client-side. Not
# actually used by this milestone's flow, which uses Stripe Checkout (a
# hosted, redirect-based page, never Stripe.js/Elements in this app) —
# prepared for a future embedded checkout.
# VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=

# --- Server-only (never VITE_ prefixed — read by api/checkout.ts and
# api/webhooks/stripe.ts via StripeProvider, never by the React app) ---
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# --- Server-only (never VITE_ prefixed — read by
# SupabaseOrderRepository / SupabaseAccessRepository, the shared
# persistence layer api/checkout.ts and api/webhooks/stripe.ts both read
# and write through, since they run as separate serverless functions with
# no shared memory. The service role key bypasses Row Level Security —
# never expose it client-side; the browser reads access through
# /api/access instead, never Supabase directly.) ---
# SUPABASE_URL=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=
